 undervalued, which is regrettable because these prayers shed light on sometimes striking aspects of early Jewish spirituality in the centuries around the turn of the era. In this volume twelve such prayers have been collected, translated, and provided with an extensive historical and philological commentary. They have been preserved on papyrus, on stone, and as part of Christian church orders into which some of them have been incorporated in a christianized from. For that reason these prayers are of great interest to scholars of both early Judaism and ancient Christianity.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGreek literaturexJewish authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aJewsxCivilizationxGreek influences. 0aJudaismvPrayers and devotionsxHistory and criticism. 0aJudaismxHistoryyPost-exilic period, 586 B.C.-210 A.D. 0aJudaismxLiturgyvTextsxHistory and criticism. 0aPrayerxJudaism. 4aGebet. 4aJüdische Spiritualität. 4aJüdisches Gebet. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh  aJewish Prayers.  aJewish Spirituality.  aPrayer.1 aNewman, Judith. H., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2008z978311021213608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWI